hey sanki monkey sanki monkeya

nanga epodhu mey aluku lungiya

hey thangi thangi enga thangiya...

hey kasu panam vandhu pogum da

utukunu oora paaka

natukunu naanga thukaa
otha adi retta vaadi paana odayaa

cutting-a potta le
bodha lam eradhu
vodafone naayiku ellam munji neelathu

hey thaniya pootu sandaya
pootu road-u la padthukuran
antha kadavul kudutha valka
elanthu avana kethukuran

hey kadana odana vangi
oruthan kalyanam panikuran
ivan thanda valathula thalaya
uttu love nu sollikuran

oru modhala moonji orthanu

kaaga usura utukura

Hey twinkle twinkle twinkle

twinkle little star-u
inaiku inaiku inaiku
setha nalaiku beer-u

hey pacha color-u jacket-a
than nachin irrukudhu
adhu side la paatha noolu
ellam pichin ikkudhu.

hey sanki monkey sanki monkeya
naanga eppodhumei aluku lungiya
hey thangi thangi enga thangiyaa
nee thuku pooda fan-a kanniya

Dei indha paatu enna padamnu theriumada.

Theriyadhu ne
Avangale solluvanga keluda
varatuma.

ivan veekaana body

vaari avale kottikura

hey theva illama rendu wife-um
veena katikuran
ooru sambalaiya gift-u
maari vangi vechukuran

antha kedu ketta keepumari

keep-a vachikuran

Elden Ring they just launch into another combo or hit you with an attack thatâ€™s so fast you barely have time to read it. Just seems like you donâ€™t really get rewarded for playing well most of the time. I Pound Down Guinness I just drank 2 Deathwish coffees to try and not have to order that stuff to see what I'd be getting into Even if that is the case people know the caffeine content and realize that and we'll come up with something stronger I definitely have to try some of that. I love coffee. My attitude with coffee is as follows; The stronger, the better. And people think that Devil Mountain is the strongest coffee in the world? Bring it on I drink death wish coffee and devil mountain coffee!! They are both great I'm 22 and have ADHD, been off my medication for almost 2 years and have been looking for alternatives as I head back into college. I've been trying a variety of these high caffeine coffees, and I intend to give this black label a try, but even brands with a lower dosage give me an adequate buzz. The biohazard brand is around 900mg and for about an hour I feel like I'm on an adderall 10mg. I think my ADHD is a variable in how I experience coffee however as I frequently hear from other people that coffee doesn't have much an effect on them. I've thought about various ways to put what ADHD feels like into words, in terms of integers it feels like this: -1/0/+1 where zero is your mind at homeostasis and -1 is your mind with ADHD. With ADHD your mind is at -1 24/7, a normal person is at 0, and +1 represents high motivation/concentration. A person that is normally at 0 while at rest should have no problem getting to +1 even without taking a stimulus, but for someone that's always at -1, it is much more difficult getting to 0 much less getting to +1. Personally at -1 my thought process feels foggy, and the mental fatigue from various tasks whether it be studying or housework sets in MUCH quicker than it would with someone at 0 or +1, what ends up happening is my mind starts searching for anything even slightly more interesting to focus my attention, sometimes it doesn't even have to be visual, it can be a random thought, and suddenly that single thought takes your mind off on a tangent and you've completely zoned out of whatever you were concentrating on just prior. At 0 or +1 that's technically still possible, but it would take a little longer. The coffee I had brings me to about .25 to .5, so slightly above 0 but not quite 1, however even then I feel much more concentrated and willing to study/work than I am at -1. I wish people could understand the difference between even -1 and 0 is major, if I were approached by a magic genie and told my mind could return to 0 indefinitely at the consequence of never reaching +1, I'd still take that offer, 0 is still much much better than -1. I didn't think much of this coffee until we perculated it in a old stainless steel percolator for 10-15min. Unreal caffeine high then, was way to much. Had about 10oz of it that way. The high last about 4 hours, was scared for a little bit. Went outside and dank cold water a few times, to try and mellow it out. Keurig didn't have this effect at all. Perculate it and unleash the devil. I dont recommend more than 1 cup this way man, I am an overnight worker, I just started drinking this stuff. Honestly yes I felt more alert than normal coffee, but it didnt make me wired. Maybe I am too laid back.. I only drink coffee black, taste was fine. A nice way to die. You guys know that your risking cardiac arrest at over 800 mg in a hour

nan Probably my favourite movie I've never seen. I recently rewatched this movie with my dad and got so much more out of it. The scene were the melted model plane undroops when the AC gets fixed made my dad and I both laugh out loud. Very rewarding to watch with someone else so we can help each other find the Whereâ€™s-Waldo-y sight gags. Thanks for the recommendation, Dunkey! dunkey being a cinephile is somehow completely unexpected and totally on brand Spiderman 3 is better though this is a fever dream I don't know why but this movie sounds like life I use this video to help me calm down and pull my mind off anxiety, thank you dunkbley This may actually be your best video This movie seems brilliant. Rather than life being a dramatic, intense, compelling sequence of scenes centered around one person, Tati portrays life as a confusing, industrialized, colorless blend of maze-like offices and imbalanced humans.

It seems like the point of this movie, apart from a criticism of over-industrialization, is that even the people who seem most professional don't really know what they're doing either. Sweet human progress! :O I remember seeing this review back in the day, but I never really thought to actively go try the game out (having not gamed much in recent years, t'all).  But WOW.  Steam had it as free to try for a few days (and only $6 for purchase after that), and I was instantly hooked.  While the game's concept and design are SO incredibly simple, and quite likely just a slight deviation on other existing phone app dungeon crawlers that I've played off and on for years.......it is a masterpiece, no question.  Anything it may have evolved from it has effectively perfected.  Even only being about 5 hrs into gameplay now (and wow, already such a HUGE difference in my skill level) I give this game EASILY an 8.5/10.  Granted, I review it on the basis of its intent and genre: is it gonna have the same level of complexity, graphics, time put in by developers, etc as something like Breath of the Wild?  Obviously not, but it's not trying to be that.  For it's genre, it deserves an 8.5, maybe even 9, out of 10.

I think, in closing, what has to be, by FAR, my favorite element of the game?........you don't directly progress further by just sinking hours into grinding, and you CERTAINLY don't have the option to "pay to win".  No, with "Enter the Gungeon", your success is measured by your skill level -both one's general, meta gaming talents, as well as specific familiarity with this game's mechanics.  There IS no "grind mindlessly" or "burn your $" options to win; if you want to win, you have to BE GOOD.   And that is something SO horrifyingly lost in practically all video games in the modern age: you don't have to demonstrate or gain actual talent or skill to win. God of War is almost more boujee than Sims4 in this sense I love how Dunkey can go from trolling the shit out of a AAA game to perfectly articulating what makes a game spectacular. From the editing to the monologues, he is a gem amongst the reviewing community ğŸ’› My only problem with game is the pacing, with the 2018 game the pacing kept flowing just between Head, Atreus and Kratos and it kept flowing but in this game they go on a mission or task and after they just go back to the house sometimes asking if you wanna go do other missions and it ruins the pacing and just puts the plot on hold and makes it suddenly go slow but thatâ€™s my opinion I still think Ragnarok is better than 2018 9/10 So just as bad as the previous one. I see. god of war is the first quadruple A type game I just realized Atreus' dialogue at 3:11 is just like the Forspken cringe trailer. You also got to fight all of the bugs and glitches. I have played every single mainline god of war game and loved them all in their own way but this game I just couldn't get through I felt after the Thor boss fight the game toned down on excitement and I got really bored don't know why when I was able to continue the entirety of 2018 but just couldn't compel myself to continue. The story seems perfect and I loved watching it but just couldn't play it myself start explaining how Sonic front got more vote than gow even though gow sold more ğŸ¤¡. I will wait. i cant play any GoW atm so I have to see some of it through videos, and i immediately recognized prozd's voice! he's an amazing VA! I can't be mad at Santa Monica for reusing the bossfights a lot in GoW4. I'm sure it's because at the time the invested most of their resources into creating the graphics, props, textures, building the game engine etc., all the base stuff. In GoW:R however they could go all out since all of the base stuff is already built, tried and tested. The only thing I didn't like about the actual gameplay was the awkward camera. Not being able to aim my attacks without moving the camera was really disorienting and made it feel like an FPS. I would have preferred only to strafe when locking on with R3, and to have the camera brought away a bit so I could actually see what I'm doing instead of getting jumped from each angle Only problem I had with it is the story. worst game I played in 2022 I think itâ€™s high art. Just because itâ€™s accessible doesnâ€™t mean the themes donâ€™t go deep. I don't quite think that the combat is fair. I'm not saying that it's all bad, just that I find it unfair.
